{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require train operators to refund tickets if no seats available",
        "additional_details": "Despite electronic ticket barriers gathering data on train usage, I believe there is insufficient seating on the majority of train journeys.\r\n \r\nRail fares increase steadily, and I think this is not a question of insufficient data but more related to rail operator profits.",
        "background": " \r\nThe Government should require train operators to refund tickets if no seats are available on trains, for at least 75% of their journey. I believe it is not acceptable for passengers to go without seating.",
